# 10. Metrics

Schema:

```text id="lxs2g3"
metrics
```

Tables:

```text id="ivm8gf"
metric_sample
```

Metric samples include:

* CPU
* RAM
* VRAM
* GPU
* latency
* queue depth
* throughput

---

# 11. Ownership Rules

Every schema belongs to exactly one service.

Only the owning service MAY:

* INSERT
* UPDATE
* DELETE

Other services SHALL communicate through:

* Events;
* public interfaces.

---

# 12. Transactions

Transactions SHALL remain local to a single schema.

Distributed transactions across services are prohibited.

Consistency between services SHALL be achieved using immutable Events.

---

# 13. Migrations

Each schema SHALL own its own migration history.

Migration execution SHALL occur during Bootstrap.

Partial migrations are prohibited.

---

# 14. Design Invariants

Invariant 1

One PostgreSQL instance.

Multiple logical schemas.

---

Invariant 2

Each service owns exactly one schema.

---

Invariant 3

Cross-schema writes are prohibited.

---

Invariant 4

Historical state is append-only whenever possible.

---

Invariant 5

Services synchronize through Events rather than shared persistence.

---

Invariant 6

Database ownership follows service ownership exactly.
